VLAN - VIRTUAL LOCAL AREA NETWORK
==================================
LAN 	- GROUP OF DEVICES WHERE LOCALLY CABLED
VLAN	- GROUP OF DEVICES WHERE ALL DEVICES RECEIVES BROADCAST
	- NETWORK ADDRESS
	- LOGICALLY DIVIDE NETWORK INTO DIFFERENT BROADCAST DOMAINS BY INFORMING THE SWITCH WHAT ARE THE GROUPS OF DEVICES IN YOUR NETWROK AND WHICH PORT DOES THESE DEVICES IS CONNECTED TO IN ITS INTERFACES.
	- EVERY GROUP IS A DIFFERENT DOMAIN


SWITCH DEFAULT:
------------------
- ONE PORT /INTERFACE = ONE COLLISION DOMAIN
- Switch is ONE BIG BROADCAST DOMAIN - floods all the port with the broadcast message.
- SWITCH IS A LAYER 2 DEVICE that FORWARD PACKET BASED ON MAC ADDRESS (SOURCE/DSRTINATION)
						     ---------------------------------


DISADVANTAGE OF A SWITCH
-------------------------
1. INEFFICIENT NETWORK CAUSE BY EXCESSIVE BROADCAST, BROADCAST SLOWS DOWN YOUR NETWORK.
2. SECURITY ISSUE


CONFIGURING VLANS
======================

WAYS TO CONFIGURE VLANS
-----------------------
1. VLAN CONFIGURATION MODE WAY
	- SUPPORTED BY NEWER CISCO SWITCHES
	- INCLUDED IN CCNA EXAM
	- SYNTAX:
		conf t
		vlan 10
		name IT
		exit

2. VLAN DATABASE MODE WAY
	- SUPPORTED BY OLDER SWITCHES
	- CONFIGURE IN ENABLE MODE
	- SYNTAX:	
		enable
		vlan database
		vlan 10 name IT
		exit
		

! If you want to reset the interface to its default state, use:
! default interface <interface_name>



SW1 USING THE VLAN CONFIGURATION MODE WAY
-----------------------------------------
1. CREATE VLAN AND VLAN NAME
conf t	
vlan 10
name IT

vlan 20
name SALES

vlan 30
name ADMIN

vlan 40 
name MARKETING
exit

VERIFY
sh vlan br

2. ASSIGN THE PORTS TO ITS PROPER VLANS - 
** YOU CAN ONLY ASSIGN AN ACCESS PORT TO A VLAN BUT NEVER TO TRUNK PORTS, 
AN ACCESS PORTS CAN ONLY BE A MEMBER OF ONE VLAN BUT A TRUNK INTERFACE IS A 
MEMBER OF ALL VLANS SUCH THAT ALL BROADCAST FROM ALL VLANS ARE SEND OUT TO ALL TRUNK INTERFACES

conf t
interface f0/4
switchport mode access
!
! TO ASSIGN THIS PORT TO VLAN 
!
switchport access vlan 10 <vlan #/id>
exit
!
! OR USE THE INT RANGE COMMAND
! USE INTERFACE RANGE COMMAND TO ASSIGN MULTIPLE SEQUENCIAL # OF INTERFACE
! #interface range fa0/4-8 command
!

conf t
interface range f0/4 -8
switchport mode access
switchport access vlan 10
no shut
exit
!

interface range f0/9 - 11
switchport mode access
switchport access vlan 20
no shut
exit
!

interface range f0/12 - 15
switchport mode access
switchport access vlan 30
no shut
exit
!

interface range f0/16 - 19
switchport mode access
switchport access vlan 40
no shut
exit

interface range f0/20-24
shutdown
exit

VERIFY
sh vlan br

! TO SHUTDOWN UNUSED PORTS
-----------------------------
conf t
interface range f0/20-24
shutdown
exit
